This is my second time using this tile mat on a kitchen backsplash and I can’t imagine tiling any other way! You simply attach the adhesive paper to the wall and then stick the tiles to it. You press the tile down into the paper for a few seconds to lock it in. Then you can grout immediately with no wait time! 

This is very beginner friendly, and a much cleaner way to tile than using traditional mortar. It is a PERMANENT tiling solution that is not renter friendly. It’s recommended for walls only, not flooring. We had it in our last kitchen for three years with absolutely no peeling or loss of adhesion. From my experience with it, I’d imagine it would be just as difficult to remove as tile that was installed with traditional mortar.

Peppermint Espresso Martini Servings: 1
Total Time: 10 Minutes Ingredients:
- 1oz. Espresso
- 2oz. Vodka
- 1oz. Kahlua
- 1/2oz. Torani Peppermint Syrup
- Crushed Peppermint Candy
- Honey
- Ice
Instructions:
- Start by rimming your glass with honey and dipping it into into the crushed peppermint
candy
- In a cocktail shaker, add ice, espresso, vodka, kahlua, and peppermint syrup. Shake
vigorously until combined and cold.
- Pour the cocktail into the prepared glass and enjoy!

This reel has been long overdue and highly requested! I’m finally sharing how I measure for my @twopagescurtains Roman shades, both inside mount and outside mount. The color I have throughout my entire home is MARBLE WHITE. Use code: MICHELLE15 for 15% off and comment SHOP for all links!

Inside mount
•Window frame must be at least 2” deep
•Measure inner width of window and subtract 3/8”
•Measure window height with no subtractions

Outside mount 
For window frame depths less than 2” 
Measure window width including mouldings and add 1/2”
Measure window height including mouldings and add 3”
